I mean presumably UBS (and Credit Suisse) is looking to take all the charge=
s it can: Better to write everything down, sell assets at a loss, reserve f=
or liabilities, etc., now, so that you can report a fluky profit of, say, $=
40 billion instead of $57 billion next quarter and then report nice profits=
